Magikhan in MT <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uancientwalkeremarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AncientwalkerEmarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(8/27/01 5:15:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://207.168.207.222/images/SidepicAW1.jpg width=200 height=350></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Orb of Mastery, Epic Pet, Info</span><hr size=1> If you can do this epic without the help of the better guilds then you must be really rich, since a PoA raid is usually an all weekend thing, involving farming and lots of costs.  (crown may cost 30-50k plat to buy)  Also the crown isn't exactly common.. You can get none after clearing the 7th island, an easy island but not a walk in the park unless you love dt's.<br>
<br>
It is my understanding that all epics cannot be completed (final hand in) until 51+, especially since you must be 51+ to chain a piece of an epic for any class.<br>
<br>
You cannot conferm the dmg, hitpoints, stun, dd of the pet in duel status because that does not have full dmg results, even against another pet.  You cannot compare it against another PC (especially a well equiped one), because the AC of that person will prevent you from getting a good read on the attack and dmg of the epic pet, since it will prolly hit for 40s or less, I know of that happening against a 60 monk.<br>
<br>
Damage shield of all pets, except the post 50s are lvl of pet +1 and the DDs are lvl of pet +2.  Again that changes in post 50.  The only real way to find out the base and dmg of epic pet stun, dd is to test it against a mob that you know has a certain amount of hp.  (Ie, found out lvl 54 water pet does rougly 75-100pts of dmg, as I tested the lvl 1 nuke on a wolf and did 75 points before it died.)  Or have something such as show eq, or you are a programmer.<br>
<br>
