<br>
Pet stats are as followed<br>
<br>
HP= 3.2k (confirmed) <br>
Hand-Hand= quad 67, 143 crit (90 percent of time he only hits triple) VERY VERY rare crit. Procs 167 dd, chance to proc on each attack.<br>
Spells.  Stun (unconfirmed look above), and spell proc. Aura of elemental mastery 50 point DS (confirmed on Bristlebane server against PC's and NPC's)<br>
Resists are all based around 100 (not percentage, 100mr,FR,CR, Unknown on Pr,DR)<br>
Bashes and kicks as well.<br>
<br>
Its been my experience that the pet isnt designed so much to be the ULITIMATE tanks as many mages think, just he cumilation of all the pets put together and a couple degrees tougher then in each aspect.  Its purpose isnt so much to stop a raging dragon from eating you alive but to add to a mages overall damage capacity.  Procs and Stuns are easly resisted by PC's and Mobs of higher lvls (54+). Average DPS (damage per second) against lower lvl mobs (53 and under) can range from 110 to 280 (with sham/ench buffs and post 56 mage buffs). Average DPS on 55-65 KUNARK and old world mobs ranges from 50-100 DPS (procs often dont hit, his attack also then plays a major role) Average damage velious 60+mobs (ToV and such not) drops to a dramaticly minimal 10-15 DPS (rarely even hits and almost never gets proc to stick).  So when it comes down to it this pet has its good side and then its HORRID side.  BTW for farming this thing rules over anything else you can think of <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uchadly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>chadly</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(9/12/01 1:18:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Orb of Mastery, Epic Pet, Info</span><hr size=1> <br>
